#### **About the Research Foundation**


The Research Foundation of The City University of New York (RFCUNY) was established as a not-for-profit educational corporation chartered by the State of New York in 1963. RFCUNY supports CUNY faculty and staff in identifying and obtaining external support (pre-award) from government and private sponsors and is responsible for the administration of all such funded programs (post-award).


RFCUNY stands between CUNY’s principal investigators (PIs) and the sponsors who support them and strives to fulfill its essential responsibilities to both groups. Working closely with individual PIs and Grants Officers on the campuses, RFCUNY oversees employment, accounting, audit, reporting, purchasing, and special responsibilities that include management of a planned giving program; liaison with governmental agencies and foundations; negotiation of agreements; facility construction and renovation; protection and commercialization of intellectual property; and compliance with applicable standards in research involving human subjects, animal care, environmental and radiological safety, and conflicts of interest.


#### **Equal Employment Opportunity Statement**


The Research Foundation of the City University of New York is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action/Americans with Disabilities Act/E-Verify Employer. It is the policy of the Research Foundation of CUNY to provide equal employment opportunities free of discrimination based on race, color, age, religion, sex, pregnancy, childbirth, national origin, disability, marital status, veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity, genetic information, marital status, domestic violence victim status, arrest record, criminal conviction history, or any other protected characteristic under applicable law.

Atlantic Medical Imaging is seeking an experienced Medical Records Clerk to join the team in the Brick, NJ office location. This is a great opportunity to apply your existing skills and knowledge and join a growing outpatient Radiology practice.


The responsibilities of the Medical Records Clerk include, but are not limited to:

* Manages incoming requests for medical records in both paper and electronic format, ensuring proper documentation and adherence to laws, regulations and company policies at all times;
* Facilitates retrieval of radiology reports for review by authorized individuals, inclusive of faxing & electronic transmission of reports;
* Maintains accurate and quality medical record files in proper sequence according to company policies and procedures;
* Accesses PACS and identifies patients' studies; prints images, or burns CD from PACS;
* Respects and maintains privacy and dignity of patient's records; always assures Patient Confidentiality;
* Always maintains HIPAA standards;
* Establishes and maintains open communication with other AMI departments and offices;
* Answers the telephones including using the available options of the telephone system and taking/relaying accurate messages immediately/efficiently.
* Retrieves voicemail messages and rerouting of phone lines (as assigned);
* Provides support and back-up to the Scheduling Department as a Scheduler in the Call Center as needed;
* Communicates with patients and callers, both in-person and through telephone calls, to gather and obtain information relating to exam including insurance information, referrals, and prescriptions;
* Maintains a clean and safe working environment; and
* Performs other duties as assigned.


The position is based in AMI's Brick, NJ office with a work schedule of Monday-Friday, 7:30am-4pm. Schedules are subject to change based on business needs.


Eligible candidates have a High School Diploma or equivalent. Medical Records experience is required for this position. Candidates must also have a basic knowledge of medical terminology. Experience with medical software and Electronic Medical Records (EMR) is required; Fuji RIS experience a plus. Candidates must have strong computer skills and are proficient in the Microsoft Office Suite. Candidates must demonstrate strong customer service skills, including excellent verbal and written communication with an exceptional telephone presence. Candidates must be highly organized with the ability to collaborate, promote inclusiveness, and effectively work within a team environment.


AMI offers a generous compensation and benefits package, including medical, prescription, dental, vision, flexible spending accounts, Paid Time Off (PTO), 401k andprofit sharing, along withthe opportunity to work in an exciting and progressive outpatient practice.


